---
import SiteShell from "../components/SiteShell.astro";
import "../styles/site.css";
---

<SiteShell
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The basic terms for using Postmerce to prepare, schedule and publish social content through connected accounts."
  eyebrow="Legal"
>
  <section class="legal-prose">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 3, 2026</p>

    <h2>Service</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce is a social publishing tool operated by Triple Muffin. The service
      helps authorized users upload media, prepare platform-specific posts, schedule
      publishing jobs and review publishing status.
    </p>

    <h2>User responsibility</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for the content you upload, schedule and publish through
      Postmerce. You must have the rights and permissions needed to publish that
      content on each selected platform.
    </p>

    <h2>Connected accounts</h2>
    <p>
      You may connect supported social accounts through OAuth. You are responsible
      for keeping platform accounts secure and for complying with each platform's
      terms, community rules, advertising rules and API policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not use Postmerce to publish unlawful, abusive, deceptive or infringing content.</li>
      <li>Do not attempt to bypass platform limits, review requirements or access controls.</li>
      <li>Do not share secrets, access tokens or credentials through support messages.</li>
      <li>Do not use Postmerce to automate accounts you do not own or control.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Availability</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce depends on connected platforms, account permissions and platform API
      availability. Features, platform support and publishing behavior may change as
      Postmerce evolves and as third-party platform APIs change.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party platforms</h2>
    <p>
      Publishing depends on third-party APIs such as YouTube, Meta, TikTok and LinkedIn.
      Postmerce cannot guarantee that a platform will accept, process, publish or keep
      available any specific post.
    </p>

    <h2>Termination and deletion</h2>
    <p>
      You may request removal of your connected account data and uploaded content. See
      <a href="/data-deletion">Data deletion</a> for the current process.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For product questions contact <a href="mailto:support@postmerce.pl">support@postmerce.pl</a>.
      For developer or API review questions contact
      <a href="mailto:developer@postmerce.pl">developer@postmerce.pl</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteShell>
